In general, for $n \le x < n + 1,$
\[\left( x - n - \frac{1}{2} \right)^2 + y^2 = \frac{1}{4}\]is the equation of a circle centered at $\left( \frac{2n + 1}{2}, 0 \right)$ with radius $\frac{1}{2}.$

