&= \sum_{k = 1}^{2010} \frac{x^{3k} - 1}{x^k (x^k - 1)}

Step 2: We are left with: $$\log_2\frac{3x+9}{x-2}=2$$Now, eliminate logs and solve: \begin{align*}
\frac{3x+9}{x-2}&=2^2\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 3x+9&=4(x-2)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 3x+9&=4x-8\\
\Rightarrow\qquad &=x\\
\end{align*}
